{"title_page": "Yukiko Fujisawa", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese figure skater}}\n{{Infobox figure skater\n| name = Yukiko Fujisawa\n| image= Fujisawa 2008JGPF by Carmichael.jpg\n| caption=  Fujisawa at the 2008\u201309 Junior Grand Prix Final.\n| altname= \n| country= [[Japan]]\n| birth_date= {{birth date and age|1995|4|14}}\n| birth_place= [[Chiba, Chiba|Chiba]]\n| residence= \n| height= {{height|m=1.49|precision=0}}\n| coach= Yumi Kono\n| formercoach= \n| choreographer= [[Kenji Miyamoto (figure skater)|Kenji Miyamoto]] \n| formerchoreographer= \n| skating club= Iizuka FSC\n| currenttraininglocations= [[Fukuoka]]\n| beganskating= 2000\n| retired= \n| combined total= 149.28\n| combined date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in the United Kingdom|2008 ISU JGP J. Curry Memorial]]\n| SP score= 50.82\n| SP date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in the United Kingdom|2008 ISU JGP J. Curry Memorial]]\n| FS score= 101.44\n| FS date= [[2008\u201309 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2008\u201309 JGP Final]]\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Yukiko Fujisawa'''|\u85e4\u6fa4 \u4eae\u5b50|Fujisawa Yukiko|extra=born April 14, 1995}} is a [[Japan|Japanese]] [[figure skater]]. She was born in [[Chiba, Chiba|Chiba]]. She is the [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in the Czech Republic|2008 JGP Czech Skate]] champion, 2009 [[ISU Junior Grand Prix Final|JGP Final]] silver medalist, and 2010 [[Japan Junior Figure Skating Championships|Japanese junior]] bronze medalist.\n\n==Programs==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n! Season\n! [[Short program (figure skating)|Short program]]\n! [[Free skating]]\n! Exhibition\n|-\n! 2011\u201312 <br> <ref name=ISU-1112/>\n|\n* [[The Cotton Club (film)|The Cotton Club]] <br> {{small| by [[John Barry (composer)|John Barry]] }}\n|\n* [[Malague\u00f1a (song)|Malague\u00f1a]] <br> {{small| by [[Ernesto Lecuona]] }}\n|\n|-\n! 2010\u201311 <br> <ref name=ISU-1011/>\n|\n* Tango <br> {{small| from [[Cirque du Soleil]] <br> by [[Ren\u00e9 Dup\u00e9r\u00e9]] }}\n|\n* [[